<title>ITALY: Italian May wage inflation 4.7 pct.</title>
<headline>Italian May wage inflation 4.7 pct.</headline>
<dateline>ROME 1997-06-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Italian wage inflation stood at an annual 4.7 percent in May, statistics institute ISTAT said in a statement.</p>
<p> ITALY HOURLY WAGE INFLATION   May 97    April 97    May 96</p>
<p> Year/year change		  +4.7%	+4.5%	+4.0%</p>
<p> Month/month change		+0.2%	+0.1%	 0.0%</p>
<p> Index (base 1995=100)	   106.2	106.0     101.4</p>
<p>Istat said wage inflation in the agriculture sector rose 1.6 percent year-on-year in May, 3.8 percent in the industrial sector, 2.5 percent in the chemical sector, 4.6 percent in the metalworkers sector, 3.5 percent in the service sector, 1.5 percent in the transport and communications sector and 7.5 percent in the public administration.</p>
<p>The statistics office added that the number of hours lost to industrial action in the first four months was a provisional 4.6 million hours from 1.4 million in May 1996.</p>
<p>-- Rome newsroom +396 6782501</p>
